cialization of metropolitan space, the interlocking dimensions of class and race in metropolitan development, and the importance of analyzing housing as a system of social stratification. In this second edition, he includes new material that explains the racially unequal impact of the subprime real estate crisis that began in late 2007, and explains why racial disparities in housing and lending remain despite the passage of fair housing laws and antidiscrimination statutes.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aHousing -- Missouri -- Kansas City -- History -- 20th century. 0aHousingzMissourizKansas CityxHistoryy20th century. 0aKansas City (Mo.) -- Economic conditions. 0aKansas City (Mo.) -- Race relations. 4aPolitics and Law : Political Sociology. 4aPublic Policy : Housing. 4aPublic Policy : Urban and Regional Planning. 4aSociology : Urban Sociology. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Discrimination & Race Relations.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2014z978311149015140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143844944940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438449449423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438449449/original  a978-3-11-149015-1  SUNY Press eBook Package 2014b2014  aGBV-deGruyter-alles